content.text: Hey, I've been sourcing silicone kitchen utensils on Alibaba for 2 years. Currently paying --.85/unit FOB Ningbo for 5000 units. My supplier raised prices and I'm looking at alternatives. Can you beat that?

content.thinking: Experienced buyer, clear specs, wants price comparison.

content.text:
$0.85/unit FOB Ningbo for silicone utensils at 5K units is a solid benchmark — your supplier had you at a competitive tier.

Price increases on silicone have been common lately (raw material + energy costs in Zhejiang). We typically see that range at $0.70-1.20/unit depending on the specific items and silicone grade.

To see if we can beat it — which utensils are in your set? (spatulas, tongs, spoons all price differently since tooling and silicone weight vary)
Full set - spatula, ladle, slotted spoon, turner, tongs, pasta server. 6 piece set. Food grade silicone with stainless steel handles. I know the product inside out. Just need a better price than 0.85

You know your product — 6-piece set with SS handles and food-grade silicone, that's a standard high-demand config. $0.85/unit at 5K is already below average for that spec, so beating it means going direct to factories with idle capacity or running a competitive quote.

What's your target destination? (Shipping cost is where deals like this get made or lost — a better unit price means nothing if freight eats it up)
